$$

Adding 1 to both sides, we get:

$$
\begin{equation*}
x^5 = -1 \,.
\end{equation*}
$$

Taking the fifth root of both sides, we find:

$$
\begin{equation*}
x = -1^{1/5} \,.
\end{equation*}
$$

Since $x$ is a real number, we take the positive root, so $x = 1$.

